<manpage>
    <sample url="datatypes\EzByteBuf\bufCopy">bufcopy</sample>
    <volume> Common Data Structure </volume>
    <interface> EzByteBuf   </interface>
    <method> Copy </method>

    <description>
        <para>Copies a new string to current byte buffer and overwrites the old data.</para>
    </description>

    <syntax>
        <return_val> int </return_val>
        <parameters>
        <api_param>
            <param_type> const void* </param_type>
            <param_name> p </param_name>
            <param_note>
                <para> Pointer to the source data to be copied.  </para>
            </param_note>
        </api_param>

        <api_param>
            <param_type> int  </param_type>
            <param_name> n </param_name>
            <param_note>
                <para> The number of bytes to be copied. </para>
            </param_note>
        </api_param>
        </parameters>
    </syntax>

    <return>
        <para>Returns the number of bytes that actually copied.</para>
    </return>

    <remarks>
        <para>Copies specialized length data to the buffer at the start address and overwrites the old data of the first n bytes. But if parameter <i>n</i> is greater than the length of buffer, then the remaining part will be cut off and returns the size of buffer.</para>
        <para>If parameter <i>p</i> equals to 0 (that means the pointer to data to be inserted is NULL), but parameter <i>n</i> unequals to 0 (that means the number of bytes to be inserted unequals to 0), then it leads to a run time error.</para>
    </remarks>

    <example><pre><![CDATA[
#include <stdio.h>
#include <ezbuf.h>

int __cdecl main()
{
    EzByteBuf_<200> buf;

    buf.Copy("Hello!", 7);

    if (!buf.IsNull()) {
        printf("%s\n", (char*)buf);
    } else {
        printf("wrong!\n");
    }

    return 0;
}
]]></pre></example>

<result><![CDATA[
Hello!
]]></result>

